<HEADLINE>
POLICE IN TAINAN BUST ILLEGAL ARSENAL, ARREST SIX MEN
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tainan, April 10 (CNA) 04/10/07  21:58:37 (By Han Nai-kuo)
</P>
<P>
Police in Tainan city uncovered an illegal arsenal Tuesday and
arrested six men belonging to a ring involved in the production
of illegal firearms and ammunition.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Tainan police station said that agents with
the criminal investigation division raided two locations in
Tainan city and Tainan County, arresting ring leader Yeh Ho-
chiang and five accomplices: Chiu Yu-chiang, Su Jen-po, Su Hsiu-
min, Huang Chao-chun and Tseng Feng-jung.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, the ring leader is a repeat offender
who had been twice arrested for violations of the Statute
Regulating Firearms, Ammunition, Knives and Other Deadly Weapons.
</P>
<P>
The agents also seized five firearms, some 100 rounds of
ammunition and more than 1,000 half-finished cartridges.
</P>
<P>
Under the Statute Regulating Firearms, Ammunition, Knives and
Other Deadly Weapons, amended in January 2005, those who produce
firearms or explosives without permission from government
authorities can be subjected to at least seven years in prison
plus a fine of NT$30 million.
</P>
